<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1436,1471,2000]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,360,1507,1532]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Type-locality.</emphasis>
Africa, corrected by 
<bibRefCitation author="Etheridge" box="[624,821,1507,1532]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" refString="Etheridge, R. E. (1968) A review of the iguanid genera Uracentron and Strobilurus. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History), Zoology, 17, 45 - 64." type="journal article" year="1968">
Etheridge (
<number box="[755,813,1507,1532]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" value="1968.0">1968</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
to the vicinity of Paramaribo, 
<collectingCountry box="[1204,1314,1507,1532]" name="Suriname" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Suriname</collectingCountry>
, and later restricted by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hoogmoed" box="[297,503,1543,1568]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" refString="Hoogmoed, M. S. (1973) Notes on the herpetofauna of Surinam. IV. The lizards and amphisbaenians of Surinam. Biogeographica, 4, 1 - 419." type="journal article" year="1973">
Hoogmoed (
<number box="[437,495,1544,1568]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" value="1973.0">1973</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
to the confluence of Cottica River and the Perica Creek, 
<collectingCountry box="[1144,1255,1543,1568]" name="Suriname" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Suriname</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
